body:
If I have to render different HTML Class with different state value, one option is to make every small HTML content a different React class and call them individually like this. 

``` javascript
var PhotoRows = React.createClass({
  render: function () {
    var container = <PublicPhotos />
    if (this.props.admin) {
      container = <PersonalPhotos/>;
    }
    return (
      <div className="row-action pull-right">
      {container}
      </div>
    ); 
  }
});
```

But when I have to add few HTML lines directly in the render function, there is no way to do something like this:

``` javascript
  var PhotoRows = React.createClass({
  render: function () {
    var container = "<a>Public Container</a>";
    if (this.props.admin) {
      container = "<a>Private Container</a>";
    }
    return (
      <div className="row-action pull-right">
      {container}
      </div>
    ); 
  }
});
```

This makes it very difficult in certain cases where there are a lot of small HTML manipulations on different state values. 

``` javascript
var PersonalInfoAboutMe = React.createClass({
  render: function () {
    if (this.props.is_admin) {
      return (
        <div className="col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 first-column">  
          <div className="user-bio card">
            <p className="heading"><span className="glyphicon glyphicon-user"></span> Short About Me</p>
              <p className="admin-data">{this.props.admin_data}</p>
            <p className="bio-content">{this.props.description}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      );
    } else {
      if (!empty(this.props.description)) {
        return (
          <div className="col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 first-column">  
            <div className="user-bio card">
              <p className="heading"><span className="glyphicon glyphicon-user"></span> Short About Me</p>
              <p className="bio-content">{this.props.description}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        );
      } else {
        return (
          <div className="col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 first-column hide">  
          </div>
        );
      }
    }    
  }
});
```

Can we have a better way to add HTML directly into the return function using some notation like  

``` javascript
{{<a> </a>}} .
```

Or is it that I am missing something here and there is actually a better way to do it in React??
